theorem subset_interior_closure_of_subset_P3
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hP3 : Topology.P3 (X := X) B) (hAB : (A : Set X) ⊆ B) :
    (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure B) := by
  intro x hxA
  have hxB : x ∈ B := hAB hxA
  exact hP3 hxB

theorem closure_subset_of_subset_interior_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} (h : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure (B : Set X))) :
    closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure B := by
  -- First, upgrade the given inclusion to `A ⊆ closure B`.
  have h₁ : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure B :=
    (Set.Subset.trans h interior_subset)
  -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
  exact closure_mono h₁

theorem subset_closure_interior_of_P1 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} (hP1 : Topology.P1 (X := X) A) :
    (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
  intro x hx
  exact hP1 hx
